# Development Workflow Guide

## Available Scripts
From [package.json](mdc:package.json):

### Development
- `npm run dev` - Start development server with Vite
- `npm run preview` - Preview production build locally

### Building
- `npm run build` - Build for production (TypeScript compilation + Vite build)

### Code Quality
- `npm run lint` - Run Biome linter
- `npm run lint:fix` - Fix auto-fixable linting issues
- `npm run lint:fix-all` - Fix all linting issues (including unsafe fixes)

## Development Environment

### TypeScript Configuration
- Main config: [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json)
- App-specific config: [tsconfig.app.json](mdc:tsconfig.app.json)
- Node-specific config: [tsconfig.node.json](mdc:tsconfig.node.json)

### Linting & Formatting
- **Biome**: Used for linting and formatting (configured in [biome.json](mdc:biome.json))
- **ESLint**: Additional ESLint configuration in [eslint.config.js](mdc:eslint.config.js)

### Build Configuration
- **Vite**: Configured in [vite.config.ts](mdc:vite.config.ts)
- **Path Aliases**: `@` maps to `/src` for clean imports
- **Tailwind**: Integrated via `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin

## Best Practices

### Import Organization
1. React and external libraries
2. Internal components and utilities
3. Relative imports for local files

### Component Structure
**CRITICAL**: Always use normal functions, never `React.FC`:

```typescript
// 1. Imports
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

// 2. Types/Interfaces
interface ComponentProps {
  title: string;
  children?: React.ReactNode;
  className?: string;
}

// 3. Component definition - ALWAYS use function, never React.FC
export function Component({ title, children, className }: ComponentProps) {
  const [state, setState] = useState(false);

  useEffect(() => {
    // component logic
  }, []);

  return (
    <div className={cn("base-classes", className)}>
      <h1>{title}</h1>
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}

// ‚ùå NEVER do this:
// export const Component: React.FC<ComponentProps> = ({ ... }) => { ... };
```

### Styling Guidelines
- Use Tailwind utility classes for styling
- Use the `cn()` utility for conditional classes
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use design system components when available
- Dark theme is default (zinc-950 backgrounds, zinc-100 text)
- Use violet-500 (#8b5cf6) for primary accents

